title: 'We are so delighted to have the President of Ireland here' - Michael D Higgins' travelled by Blackhawk to FARC rebel army in Colombia jungle
text: News State Visits Monday 13 February 2017 'We are so delighted to have the President of Ireland here' - Michael D Higgins' travelled by Blackhawk to FARC rebel army in Colombia jungle Ryan Nugent 0 Comments Share 'We are so delighted to have the President of Ireland here' - Michael D Higgins' travelled by Blackhawk to FARC rebel army in Colombia jungle Independent.ie President Michael D Higgins was left waiting at a military base outside the city of Medellin due to heavy fog on Sunday night - as the Colombian air force made attempts to take him to visit the notorious FARC rebel army in the jungle.  news/state-visits/we-are-so-delighted-to-have-the-president-of-ireland-here-michael-d-higgins-travelled-by-blackhawk-to-farc-rebel-army-in-colombia-jungle-35444903.html http://www.independent.ie/incoming/article35444915.ece/43d79/AUTOCROP/h342/higgins%20.jpg President Higgins at the Military air base as he waited for cloud cover to clear President Michael D Higgins was left waiting at a military base outside the city of Medellin due to heavy fog on Sunday night - as the Colombian air force made attempts to take him to visit the notorious FARC rebel army in the jungle.
